For the "Government Districts" (Regierungsbezirke), see Regierungsbezirk. {{#invoke: Sidebar | collapsible }} The districts of Germany are known as German: Landkreise, except in the states of North Rhine-Westphalia and Schleswig-Holstein where they are known simply as German: ''Kreise'' . It would make them second level administrative subdivisions in 12 of the 16 states and third level administrative subdivsions in 4 of the 16 states."@en
